videos.description: 1H (12:57) DUKE Grayson Allen made Three Point Jumper.
videos.headline: G. Allen made Three Point Jumper.

videos.description: Donovan Mitchell penetrates and finds Ray Spalding for a big dunk.
videos.headline: Spalding makes Duke pay with big slam

videos.description: The Blue Devils have made 6 of their 11 long-range attempts, including this Grayson Allen triple to put them back in front in Louisville.
videos.headline: Duke heating up from downtown

videos.description: Duke G Grayson Allen hits a 3-pointer just before the first half buzzer sounds to give the Blue Devils an 8-point lead over Louisville heading into halftime.
videos.headline: Grayson Allen beats first half buzzer with 3

videos.description: As he's falling to the floor, Duke G Grayson Allen throws up a shot that miraculously finds the bottom of the net.
videos.headline: Grayson Allen's awkward shot somehow falls

videos.description: 2H (13:31) DUKE Grayson Allen made Three Point Jumper.
videos.headline: G. Allen made Three Point Jumper.

videos.description: Louisville F Jaylen Johnson is called for a technical foul after striking Duke G Grayson Allen in the face while fighting for a loose ball.
videos.headline: Louisville's Johnson hit with T after striking Allen in face

videos.description: 2H (12:26) DUKE Marshall Plumlee made Dunk. Assisted by Grayson Allen.
videos.headline: M. Plumlee made Dunk. Assisted by G. Allen.

videos.description: Duke C Marshall Plumlee beats the Louisville defense down the court and throws down an emphatic one-handed slam.
videos.headline: Marshall Plumlee's ferocious dunk

videos.description: 2H (7:35) LOU Damion Lee made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Trey Lewis.
videos.headline: D. Lee made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by T. Lewis.

videos.description: After trailing for most of the game, Louisville G Damion Lee his a 3-pointer to give the Cardinals a one-point lead over Duke.
videos.headline: Lee's 3 puts Louisville in front

videos.description: Coach K gets called for his first technical foul since March 16, 2014 against Virginia.
videos.headline: Coach K gets T'd up

videos.description: Louisville's Damion Lee looks forward to his final games with the Cardinals and describes dislocating his finger before the physical game against Duke.
videos.headline: Damion Lee hopes to bring ACC title to Louisville
